<document><title><tag>intersection</tag> component</title>

<section><title>Associated Attributes</title>
<ul>
  <li>none at this time</li>
</ul>

</section>


<section><title>Description</title>
  <p>The <tag>intersection</tag><idx><tag>intersection</tag></idx> component renders a point when nested inside a <ref><tag>graph</tag></ref> component, and renders a coordinate pair in the form <m>(a,b)</m> otherwise. It may be used alone, or nested inside a <ref><tag>point</tag></ref> component, but can only be labeled with a point label. Current functionality supports generation of intersections in <m>\mathbb{R^2}</m> through user-specification of a single pair of lines. See examples below. </p>
</section> 
  
<section><title>Usage Examples</title>

<tabular top="medium">
  <row bottom="minor">
    <cell>
<subsection><title>Sample DoenetML code:  Define an intersection</title>
<pre>
<tag>p</tag>Two intersecting lines:<tag>/p</tag>
<tag>graph</tag>
  <tag>point name="A" label="A"</tag>(-5,-5)<tag>/point</tag>
  <tag>point name="B" label="B"</tag>(2,2)<tag>/point</tag>
  <tag>line name="AB" through="<text>$</text>A <text>$</text>B"/</tag>
  <tag>point name="C" label="C"</tag>(-1,1)<tag>/point</tag>
  <tag>point name="D" label="D"</tag>(2,-2)<tag>/point</tag>
  <tag>line name="CD" through="<text>$</text>C <text>$</text>D"/</tag>
  <tag>point label="I.P."</tag>
    <tag>intersection</tag><text>$</text>AB <text>$</text>CD<tag>/intersection</tag>
  <tag>/point</tag>
<tag>/graph</tag>
<tag>p</tag>The intersection of line AB and CD is:
<tag>intersection</tag><text>$</text>AB <text>$</text>CD<tag>/intersection</tag><tag>/p</tag>
</pre>
 
  </subsection>
    </cell>
  </row>
<!--*******************************************************-->

  
  <row bottom="medium">
    <cell>
<subsection><title>What Doenet Renders:</title>
<p>Two intersecting lines:</p>
<graph>
  <point name="A" label="A">(-5,-5)</point>
  <point name="B" label="B">(2,2)</point>
  <line name="AB" through="$A $B" />
  <point name="C" label="C">(-1,1)</point>
  <point name="D" label="D">(2,-2)</point>
  <line name="CD" through="$C $D" />
  <point label="I.P.">
    <intersection>$AB $CD</intersection>
  </point>
</graph>
<p>The intersection of line AB and CD is:
<intersection>$AB $CD</intersection></p>
</subsection>
    </cell>
  </row>
</tabular>  


<!--*******************************************************-->

